article.description: — Ben Burnham had 16 points in Charleston (SC)'s 90-67 win against Campbell on Saturday.
article.headline: Charleston (SC) defeats Campbell 90-67
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- — Ben Burnham had 16 points in Charleston (SC)'s 90-67 win against Campbell on Saturday. Burnham was 6 of 10 shooting (3 for 6 from 3-point range) for the Cougars (15-6, 6-2 Coastal Athletic Association). Jordan Crawford scored 13 points while shooting 5 for 10, including 2 for 7 from beyond the arc. Bryce Butler and Reyne Smith both finished with 12 points. Jasin Sinani led the way for the Fighting Camels (10-11, 4-4) with 21 points and seven rebounds. Campbell also got 11 points and four assists from Laurynas Vaistaras. Colby Duggan also had 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
